'''Polish Medical Association''' (Polish: ''Polskie Towarzystwo Lekarskie'') is a scientific society created in 1951, bringing together physicians of different specialties.<ref>[http://www.ptl.org.pl/Home.aspx The website]</ref> The society refers to the tradition of medical societies in [[Vilnius]] (''Towarzystwo Lekarskie Wileńskie'', from 1805) and [[Warsaw]] (''Towarzystwo Lekarskie Warszawskie'', from 1820).<ref>Brzeziński T., red.: Historia medycyny. Warszawa: Wydawnictwo Lekarskie PZWL, 1995.</ref>

The president of Polish Medical Association is Professor [[Waldemar Kostewicz]].<ref>[http://www.ptl.org.pl/MainTabs/Wladze/Czlonkowie.aspx Main Board]</ref> In the structure of the Society, there are branches, circles and sections <ref>[http://www.ptl.org.pl/MainTabs/StrukturaOrg/Oddzialy.aspx Branches]</ref><ref>[http://www.ptl.org.pl/MainTabs/StrukturaOrg/Kola.aspx Circles]</ref><ref>[http://www.ptl.org.pl/MainTabs/StrukturaOrg/Sekcje.aspx Sections]</ref> and the main seat is in [[Warsaw]].<ref>[http://www.ptl.org.pl/MainTabs/Statut.aspx Statutes]</ref>

